cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for anonymization of clinical data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with sensitive data detection and classification, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of deep learning models such as BERT and pre-trained language models suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves experiments with clinical datasets, which could also place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
